snippet: Fox News anchors appeared less than jubilant as other network anchors repeated the “too close to call” mantra early on.
abstract: Alessandra Stanley The TV Watch column holds that Fox News was the most entertaining venue for election results, as conservative commentators sullenly grappled with hard facts that on most other days are skewed towards the network's viewership.
lead_paragraph: Fox News anchors appeared less than jubilant as other network anchors repeated the “too close to call” mantra early on.

headline.print_headline: From Frustrated to Nervous, Television Networks’ Moods Explain Results
